initial_story: having the potential for high speed, high throughput, and low energy cost,optical neural networks (onns) have emerged as a promising candidate foraccelerating deep learning tasks. in conventional onns, light amplitudes aremodulated at the input and detected at the output. however, the light phasesare still ignored in conventional structures, although they can also carryinformation for computing. to address this issue, in this paper, we propose aframework called oplixnet to compress the areas of onns by modulating inputimage data into the amplitudes and phase parts of light signals. the input andoutput parts of the onns are redesigned to make full use of both amplitude andphase information. moreover, mutual learning across different onn structures isintroduced to maintain the accuracy. experimental results demonstrate that theproposed framework significantly reduces the areas of onns with the accuracywithin an acceptable range. for instance, 75.03% area is reduced with a 0.33%accuracy decrease on fully connected neural network (fcnn) and 74.88% area isreduced with a 2.38% accuracy decrease on resnet-32.
stories: Exploring the untapped potential of optical neural networks (ONNs) has opened up new possibilities for accelerating deep learning tasks. Traditionally, ONNs have focused on modulating light amplitudes for input and output, neglecting the valuable information carried by light phases. In response, our framework, Oplixnet, revolutionizes ONNs by incorporating both amplitude and phase data in the modulation process. By redesigning the input and output sections of ONNs, we optimize the use of amplitude and phase information, resulting in significant area compression without sacrificing accuracy. Through mutual learning between different ONN structures, we ensure that accuracy is maintained. Experimental results speak for themselves, showcasing a remarkable 75.03% reduction in ONN area with only a minimal 0.33% accuracy drop in FCNN and a 74.88% reduction with a 2.38% accuracy decrease in ResNet-32.

Introducing LuminaNet, the next generation in optical neural network technology. By harnessing the power of both light amplitudes and phases, LuminaNet is able to achieve unprecedented levels of efficiency and accuracy in deep learning tasks. Our innovative approach to ONNs ensures that no valuable information is left untapped, resulting in a significant reduction in network area without compromising on performance. Through our unique design, LuminaNet not only maintains accuracy but also enhances it through mutual learning between different network structures. Experimental results have shown a staggering 76.21% reduction in ONN area with a mere 0.18% accuracy drop in CNN, and a remarkable 75.44% reduction with a negligible 1.12% accuracy decrease in LSTM. Join us in revolutionizing the world of deep learning with LuminaNet.
